text: Kumukunsi is a traditional Filipino deep-fried doughnut originating from the Maguindanao people. It is made from rice flour, duck eggs, and sugar. It is traditionally fried into spiral shapes. It has a creamy flavor, similar to pancakes. ==See also== *Binangkal *Lokot-lokot *Panyalam *Shakoy == References == Category:Doughnuts Category:Philippine snack food
title: Kumukunsi
